summary: I had a cute pokemon related thought that I had to share.  So please imagine, it’s sometime in the future, Ash has moved on to...
body:
I had a cute pokemon related thought that I had to share.

So please imagine, it’s sometime in the future, Ash has moved on to yet another region, or perhaps he’s back visiting Alola.

They end up fighting against some kind of powerful legendary that’s threatening the world, as one does when they’re Ash. But it’s too powerful, it keeps knocking them down, even their combined powers aren’t doing much.

Then a worm hole open up in the sky and a large purple pokemon comes flying through and the other pokemon has no idea what hit it and suddenly Ash’s side is winning.

Eventually the threat is neutralized and Ash is able to get a close look at the pokemon that came to their aid and realizes he’s seen it before but he can’t put his finger on where.

“Ash!” it cries out telepathically, in a soft, happy voice. “Pikachu I missed you!” And as it’s nuzzling him he suddenly realizes why it’s familiar. It’s the Poipole he left back in Ultra Space all those years ago, except now grown up and a Naganadel.
